        <body>
            <div type="poem">
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1827-28" script="cursive" medium="pencil"/>now must we leave poor <persName type="fictional" corresp="#MTACKET">martin</persName> there</l>
                    <l>while we relate the <placeName type="fictional" corresp="#TOWEROFGLENDEARG">tower</placeName>s fare</l>
                    <l>a band of english soldiers marched</l>
                    <l>close by the <placeName type="fictional" corresp="#TOWEROFGLENDEARG">tower</placeName> and as they<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="28" unit="chars"/>passed</l>
                    <l>good <persName type="fictional" corresp="#ELSPETGLENDINNING">dame glendinning</persName> her sons led</l>
                    <l>out from the gate and thus she<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="29" unit="chars"/>said</l>
                    <l>no means of fighting have I on<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="25" unit="chars"/>this land</l>
                    <l>and I am at the mercy of your<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="25" unit="chars"/>hand</l>
                    <l>the <persName type="fictional" corresp="#STAWARTHBOLTON">serjeant</persName><ref type="gloss_textual" target="monastery_glosses_textual.php#SERJEANTGLOSS"/> of the troop<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="11" unit="chars"/>replied<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="monastery_glosses_contextual.php#SERJEANTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>though I have means of fighting<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>on my side</l>
                    <l>I scorn with women now to stri<subst><add rend="overwriting">v</add><del>f</del></subst>e</l>
                    <l>go to your <placeName type="fictional" corresp="#TOWEROFGLENDEARG">tower</placeName> again and live</l>
                    <l>yet dame I own I envy you</l>
                    <l>that <del rend="smudged">I</del> <persName type="fictional" corresp="#EDWARDGLENDINNING">little rogue</persName> with eyes<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="27" unit="chars"/>so blue</l>
                    <l>and will you come with<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>me my lad</l>
                    <l>the <persName type="fictional" corresp="#STAWARTHBOLTON">serjeant</persName> of the troop he<lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="26" unit="chars"/>said</l><!-- ABOVE -->
                    <l>no said the blue eyed <persName type="fictional" corresp="#EDWARDGLENDINNING">edward</persName> no</l>
                    <l>because you are to us a foe</l>
                    <l>not only that but then<lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="19" unit="chars"/>you are</l><!-- ABOVE -->
                    <l>a heretic and fond of war</l>
                    <l>why god a mercy <persName type="fictional" corresp="#STAWARTHBOLTON">old stawarth</persName><lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="25" unit="chars"/>did say</l><!-- ABOVE -->
                    <l>I see alone I must go my way</l>
                    <pb/>
                    <l>but stay <persName type="fictional" corresp="#HALBERTGLENDINNING">thou black eyed</persName> come<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="29" unit="chars"/>with me</l><!-- with BELOW me ABOVE  HOW DO WE MARK THIS UP?-->
                    <l>and many a fine sight thou<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>shalt see</l>
                    <l>no cried the furious <persName type="fictional" corresp="#HALBERTGLENDINNING">halbert</persName><lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="27" unit="chars"/>no</l><!-- ABOVE-->
                    <l>bcause thou art to us a foe</l>
                    <l>and when Im older thou<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>shalt see</l>
                    <l>the effects of my fathers<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>sword on thee</l>
                    <l>why again god a mercy<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/><persName type="fictional" corresp="#STAWARTHBOLTON">old stawarth</persName> did say</l>
                    <l>I see that alone I must<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>go my way</l>
                    <l>but stay heres a token<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>that if some men</l>
                    <l>come riding down<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>this narrow glen</l>
                    <l>they may know that<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>you are under my</l>
                    <l>protection. then I say<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>goodbye</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
